<br>
Right now I'm putting a fair amount of time into alternate advancement.  By the time i hit level 55, I hope to have about 18 AA points total, with 12 to spend.  <br>
<br>
Looking at the abilities, I think this is what I would like to spend them on, eventually:<br>
<br>
1. Run Speed 3 - This I already have.  I think it's great, it's very nice to not have to worry about being outrun when I'm injured (for the most part).  <br>
<br>
2. Innate Natural Wisdom 5 - Why? because with 10 extra wisdom, I can wear a mask, earring or ring that is exclusively for resists, such as a velium diamond wedding ring.<br>
<br>
3. Mental Clarity III.  This is the first archetype I plan on practicing. The extra mana regeneration will be wonderful.<br>
<br>
4. Healing Gift III. It's a prerequisite to many cleric archetypes.  I'm not sure when I'll practice this one, 5 and 6 below are also very attractive.<br>
<br>
5. Spell Casting Mastery. Anything to reduce fizzles. Fizzling a complete heal may mean the difference between a tank living and dying.<br>
<br>
6. Spell Casting Reinforcement. Getting a little more out of buffs is very important.<br>
<br>
I don't want to look any further ahead, because it will be a while before I get into the cleric archetypes.<br>
<br>
I know this is pretty ambitious but I think it's something to look forward to.  <br>
<br>
Anyone have any comments on other skills they would like to study? Perhaps something that I've missed?  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.inkbard.com/art/lanandaisysig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
