I agree this is a waste of 5 aa points. Personally I sit at about 270 wis in normal gear (aka 255), switching out to resist gear brings me down to 240 or so. However in a raid situation you will usually have kei on... that happily brings you up to 255 again.<br>
<br>
I used my other 3 general aa points getting regen3, just because its the hardest of the abilities for a cleric to get on gear.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>3. Mental Clarity III. This is the first archetype I plan on practicing. The extra mana regeneration will be wonderful.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
MC1 is worth the 2 points, I didnt bother going MC2. Before you seriously consider doing MC3 I would suggest working on your 8th coldain shawl... much more bang for buck there.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>4. Healing Gift III. It's a prerequisite to many cleric archetypes. I'm not sure when I'll practice this one, 5 and 6 below are also very attractive<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I am currently working on HG3, the celestial regeneration aa you can get in the class level uses this as a prerequisite, and at levels 63+ you can get upgrades to celestial regeneration that make it REALLY nice (800hp per tic regen... mana free insta cast)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>5. Spell Casting Mastery. Anything to reduce fizzles. Fizzling a complete heal may mean the difference between a tank living and dying<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I have SCM1, currently, not for the fizzles but for the reduced mana cost it can trigger. I plan on getting SCM3 once I have hit 65.<br>
