[32 Cleric]  <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=456569">Thera</a> (High Elf) Firiona Vie</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yarmeq>Yarm EQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/21/03 2:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=89.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> My take</span><hr size=1> I don't have much of a new angle to add, except for my experience with PoP abilities.  My 35 AAs have gone into Run 3, Innate Wis3 (just for the heck of it), MC3, SCR 1, MBG, Radiant Cure 1, and Divine Arbitration 1.<br>
<br>
What you do with your Archetype abilities seems to vary with your play style.  I went for mana regen with MC3 (also have Flowing Thought VI) and I have never looked back.  <br>
<br>
Mass Group Buff is the best thing I've ever gotten, of course, but don't overlook Radiant Cure and Divine Arbitration when you are looking for something to do.  They both have low AA costs and have proven very useful for me.  As an added plus, they both refresh in a mere 3 minutes!  <br>
<br>
Radiant Cure 1 takes down just about everything you're likely to encounter in an experience group.  Tash, most slows, DoTs, even snare and mez (not charm, though, since you can't cast helpful spells on charmed party members)!  Being able to knock off almost any harmful spell that hits your party is very useful.<br>
<br>
Divine Arbitration is one of the most surprisingly useful abilities I have.  It casts in under a second, and can save the day in many situations.  If I have a CH rolling on the tank, and he suddenly takes more damage than I expected, I can dismount, stop my CH, and use Divine Arbitration all in about a second.  If the rest of the group is full health and the tank is at 15% or so, it usually takes everyone in the party to about 80% at the first level of the ability (that's not exact, of course.  It will vary with your groups).  That's much faster and much more effective than using fast heals to get the tank back to a CH-safe level.<br>
<br>
Wayren Theheckami, 65 Archon of Bristlebane - Povar<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=521499">www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...num=521499</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yarmeq>Yarm EQ</A> at: 7/21/03 2:20 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blakkon>blakkon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 720<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/21/03 5:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=89.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My take</span><hr size=1> Don't completely discard MC3, after all how much would you pay for  a FT 3 item?  Cheapest in the bazaar is usually Boots of Flowing Slime at about 100 k pp. <br>
