<br>
Let's do some math on SCM vs MC, using three 58 clerics at probably the bottom of the &quot;average 58 cleric&quot; range, the top of that range, and in a top-end raid guild situation.  As a review, MC1-3 add 1 point of mana regen per level of the MC ability.  SCM adds 3%, 6% (cumulative, so 3% more) and 12% (cumulative, so 6% more) to mana savings per spell cast, including complete heals, etc.  (It might be 2% 6% 12%, but SCM3 is 12% everywhere I've seen and heard).<br>
<br>
Cleric #1 usually doesn't have KEI, spends most of his time medding or on a horse/lizard, and does have Blessed Armor of the Risen at 58 (one reason why I did my first major AAs at 58... it adds 6/tick to your mana regen, that's double mental clarity 3... so I'd get 58 before you do AAs).  He has flowing thought I, from the solstice earring, like pretty much every other 50-something cleric.  His mana regen per tick, sitting there medding/horsing is 1+1+25+6+1=34.  (1 for standing, 1 for sitting, 25 for meditating, 6 for Blessed Armor, 1 for FT1).<br>
<br>
Cleric #2 usually has KEI, spends most of her time medding or on horse, has BAotR, and has FT6.  Solistice earring, 8th shawl, and book from the big camel/giraffe/goat/whatever thing in umbral plains).  Her mana regen per tick,  medding is 1+1+25+6+14+6=53.<br>
<br>
Cleric #3 usually has VoQ, spends most of his time on a horse, has BAoTR, has beastlord mana buffs, has FT15, has Lunar Whispers, and has Wind of Marr playing for (not sure of the total with instrument modifiers, but it's 21 before modifiers, so that's worst-case scenario) 21.  His mana regen per tick medding is 1+1+25+6+18+8+15+2+21=97.<br>
<br>
Cleric #1 would increase his mana regen from 34 to 35 with MC1, an increase of just under 3%.  If he chose SCM1 instead, he'd save 3% mana on every spell he cast.  That results in an effective mana pool increase of just over 3%.  (If you went OOM from casting 97 spells before, they now cost 3% less, so you can cast 100 for the price of 97, your effective mana pool went up by 3/97 or just over 3%).  In addition, though, since you save 3% mana, if you cast a series of spells that used to put you OOM, you now have 3% mana left.  It takes you 3% less time to recover from casting a certain series of spells.  Cleric #1 has a regen rate of 34 per tick, and 3% of that is just over 1 extra point of mana per tick (effective).  SCM1 basically gives Cleric #1 a tiny bit more mana-regen for the buck compared to MC1, but also inreases his effective mana pool by 3%.  SCM1 is the better deal.  SCM2 costs twice the AA points as MC1, but provides the same benefit as SCM1.  It's probably a tossup.  Same mana pool increase from both, more or less, but for double the cost, SCM2 also increases effective mana pool again.  SCM3 provides double the benefit as SCM1 and 2 for 3 times the points as SCM1/MC1.  Double the effective mana regen and also 6% mana pool increase for 3 times as many points as MC1.  I'd still say it's worth it for this cleric.  After that, consider MC1.  MC2?  no way is it better than SCM1 2 or 3.  MC3 at 6 points is a joke.  There are lots of better AA abilities than that.<br>
<br>
Cleric #2 would raise mana regen from 53 to 54 with MC1, less than a 2% increase, or less than 1% per AA point.  As we saw above, SCM1 will give a 3% increase to effective mana regen, so 3% of 53 is 1.6 (significantly higher than the 1 point from MC1).  Or think of it as an increase of 1.5% per AA point.  In addition, the same 3% mana pool increase.  SCM2 gives another 1.6 mana per tick effective for 4 points.  That's 80% as good as MC1 but you get another 3% mana pool increase, so I'd say SCM2 is still considerably better than MC1 for this cleric.  Finally, SCM3 is a 6% increase for 6 points.  Definitely better than MC1 in value per AA point even if it didn't increase the mana pool.<br>
<br>
Cleric #3 would raise mana regen from 97 to 98 with MC1, just over a 1% increase, or about 0.5% per AA point.  SCM1 will give them approximately an equivalent of FT3 increase (3% of 97).  That blows MC1 away.  SCM2 is the same increase but for double the points.  Still, 3 for 4 points beats 1 for 2 points.  SCM3 gives about 6 extra mana per tick effective for 6 points.  6 for 6 beats 1 for 2 as well.  Hands down, SCM1-3 are more important for this cleric even completely ignoring effective mana pool increase.<br>
<br>
By the way, you can use this to analyze if an obulus death shroud (mana preservation 3) is a better upgrade than boots of flowing slime.  The ODS doesn't work on complete heals, making it complicated, but for all other spells, 10% mana savings vs FT3, it's about equal, and the ODS costs much, much less.<br>
<br>
Summary - SCM is significantly better than MC for a majority of clerics in terms of mana savings and mana pool.  The higher your mana regen is, the more effective SCM becomes.  Do SCM3 before MC, and MC will just be that much more valuable when you do it, too.<br>
<br>
Since a lot of crit heals are wasted, one can argue adept is better than gift.  Crits are fun, though, and even crits from gift 1 are double, so hey.  Still, I'd recommend if you're going to do them all, max out adept before gift (but do your 2 points in gift for fun, it's only 2 points and you'd do them eventually anyway) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Also, both adept and gift apply to procs on items which heal, too (but not clicked items like velious quest greaves).  Blackstar, Mace of Night procs for 124 for me instead of 105, and crits for 248 on average of once per proc in a full group (16% crit chance, 6 people healed, so roughly 1 crit per proc).  They're great skills.  I'm at 73 AAs, don't have MC1 yet, and still have lots to do before I do MC1.  Even more before I do MC2 or 3.  They sound better at first read than they actually are, I think. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.visi.com/~mlm/eq/gravely/signature/sig_top.gif" style="border:0;"alt="Gravely Mistaken"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
