 <p>Nina.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;img src=http://majykmykel.tripod.com/Saga/signatures/kaninasig.jpg&gt;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elhanamistfall>ElhanaMistfall</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.mistfits.com/tgrobb/elhanaportsmall.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Hospital with a pony tail</span><br>  Posts: 250<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/27/03 8:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=89.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My take</span><hr size=1> heh..<br>
<br>
Can you believe it, 5 months almost to the day after I made that post, I dinged 55. Seconds earlier, I had just dinged my 12th saved AA point.<br>
<br>
I ended up taking Spellcasting Mastery 3. Thanks everyone for the suggestions =)<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.inkbard.com/art/lanandaisysig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:black;font-family:garamond;font-size:xx-small;"> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=753930">Elhana - Venerable Templar of Tunare</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> -- Daisyfoot - 33rd Season ProudFoot (retired), Tomato Farmer</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gravely>Gravely</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/27/03 10:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=89.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.visi.com/~mlm/eq/gravely_face_60x60.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My take</span><hr size=1> Congrats on 55 and SCM3! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Have you noticed the difference yet?  Did you buy SCM 1-3 all at once?  I imagine it made a pretty big difference if you did it that way?  Any plans for what's next as far as AAs or levels or some of each?<br>
<br>
Another &quot;big difference&quot; level for me was 58, because of Blessed Armor of the Risen (the 6 extra mana per tick), and because I did SCM3 on that level.<br>
<br>
Hey, for anyone who is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>not</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> a spellbook completist, and looking at spells and AAs around the level 60 mark, I would seriously recommend flying past 60 right up to 62.  Aego is really not worth it except for completeness, because it seriously lacks hitpoints compared to the 61-2 spells.  For example, Symbol of Kazad (level 61, 910 hitpoints) plus Faith (level 61, 520 hitpoints, 22AC) plus Ward of Gallantry (level 61, 54AC) add up to 1430 hitpoints and 76AC.  That's 330 more hitpoints and 22 more AC than Aegolism (level 60, 1100 hitpoints, 54AC).  It's even 280 more hitpoints and 16 more AC than Blessing of Aegolism (level 60, 1150 hitpoints, 60AC, group spell).<br>
<br>
My point is, Aegolism is good for one level, and once you hit 61, it's out of date.  If your groupmates can put up with you not having Aego for one quick level (60 goes much faster than 59 and 61), and if you can stand buffs that only last about an hour, you can give your group much better protection at level 61 than Aego gives.  Technically, the three level 61 spells are better than Virtue at 62, but it's only 25 hitpoints difference and 4 AC difference.  Aegolism's convenient, but it's noticeably inferior to level 61 spells, and then it's probably worth going for 62 to get Virtue for the convenience.<br>
<br>
61 and 62 are huge, huge levels for clerics.  They give you access to:<br>
<br>
* Great hitpoint/ac buffs at 61, though short duration.<br>
* Virtue at 62 for convenience and good hp/ac.<br>
* Supernal Remedy at 61 (1522 hitpoints in <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>1.8 seconds</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> for 400 mana)<br>
* Supernal Elixir at 62 (2000 hitpoints healed over 4 ticks for 400 mana)<br>
* Divine Arbitration (level 1 takes the group's total damage, adds 20% and shares it evenly among the group, very fast (0.75 seconds), so it's great for saving people, and it's really a must-have ability)<br>
* Radiant Cure (cures curses, poisons and diseases for all party members, plus cures other detrimental effects like root, snare, malo(s(i(ni(a)))), etc.)<br>
* and a few other PoP abilities as well<br>
<br>
I really think the big cleric levels which seem to be good for stopping for AAs are 56, 58, 62.  65 is a nice level, too but it's the last one, so everyone who reaches it stops for AAs I think. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elsbetsquishytoes>elsbet squishytoes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Grey</span><br>  Posts: 979<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/31/03 5:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=89.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My take</span><hr size=1> Addendum, several months and levels later.<br>
<br>
I am now 61 with 32 AAs spent.  I stood at 60 for a very long time, cruised through a bunch of AAs rather quickly.  Noticed that when I leveld to 61, I had an automatic plus 5 to all stats, which is so good, and I got the (purchased, for 251 pp,) Supernal Remedy, which has been especially nice right now.  Just over 1500hp heal, for 400 mana, and 1.8 second cast time.<br>
<br>
All the best of our AAs are to heal better and faster.  SCM3 is godly.  Not flashy at all, but it does its thing.  Didn't spend anything on SCF, yeah, it's all flashy and kaboooom, over 1k damage under level 60 and all, but that isn't me.  MC1 was a good AA to get early on, Nina, you did well there.  Flowing Thought is always nice, but MC2 and 3 are debatable, based on what I've read.  Spent some points on ND1, SCR1, innate wisdom1, and I will blow a bunch more on wisdom and Pop wisdom, cos mana pool is probably the most important thing for the game I play... Saving 9 points for mass group buff seems a bit wasteful to me, since I don't raid.  <br>
<br>
But looking at Gravely's must-haves, Divine Arbitration and Radiant Cure are my goals, after I hit 62, since I have a Virtue scroll in the bank. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gravely>Gravely</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/1/03 9:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=89.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.visi.com/~mlm/eq/gravely_face_60x60.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My take</span><hr size=1> I really think you'll enjoy being 62 and getting some AAs at that level.  It's a good choice, in my opinion. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   You'll have all the buffs anyone really needs, too.<br>
<br>
The only things that I really, really love about 65 are armor of the zealot (it's 450 hitpoints and 8 mana per tick), Yaulp 6 for soloing, and Mark of the Righteous because it's so much damage.  I have never once cast The Silent Command or whatever that level 65 AE stun is.  Group Virtue is convenient, but doesn't increase my power as a cleric (and I don't raid much and accordingly don't have MGB).  It's a good level, and fun to be 65 and stuff, but I don't think there's any big reason to level up to 65 before doing AAs, especially the really important AAs. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Oh, there's also a good group heal at 64, it's like 2750 per person or so, I think, and with healing AAs and stuff, I'm getting over 3k per heal, with crits for 6500ish.  It's a good upgrade to group complete heal because it's so fast.  But it's not usually a spell I memorize except in specific situations.<br>
<br>
I'm working on avoidance AAs now (combat agility and lightning reflexes after that) because I get hit a lot and want to be able to channel more (if they're missing me, they're not interrupting me).  Then maybe channeling focus, and then, I'm not sure.  Mana pool is kind of nice, but for grinding or for long fights, mana regen is more important.  I may work on those, or I might do something like Unfailing Divinity for fun.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elhanamistfall>ElhanaMistfall</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.mistfits.com/tgrobb/elhanaportsmall.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Hospital with a pony tail</span><br>  Posts: 258<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/4/03 1:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=89.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My take</span><hr size=1> I took SCM3 right at 55. I killed a Xi Vius in Maiden's Eye and dinged AA 18, then went down to Great Divide and killed an Ancient Shardwurm and dinged 55, in that exact order ( I had been carefully splitting AA and XP, trying to get a &quot;double ding&quot; with one kill.. I have yet to be successful, but it's fun trying). Then I spent all my points on SCM and zoned into Thurg to get them to activate. I noticed a HUGE difference immediately. With KEI and SCM3, I can heal almost non-stop all the time, unless my group is being silly and fighting for aggro. I can even melee/mark of retribution/summon Smashy the amazing smashing hammer too without any ill effects. It's great fun.<br>
<br>
I should have enough for anther AA soon (tomorrow maybe?) and I plan on taking a &quot;me&quot; AA, something I'll enjoy. I've been thinking of Spellcasting Fury, just because I get a fair number of chances to be &quot;battle cleric&quot; and I think it might be fun. I was also thinking of getting crit heals, because those are pretty flashy too. Not sure what I'll take yet.<br>
<br>
I'd like to take a bunch of the different archetype AAs. I know it'll be a long process, but I'd like to get 5 or 6 a level between now and 60 so that I can have some fun. The two healing abilities, spellcasting reinforcement, mental clarity, and channeling focus are all on my list. I hope to get two of them to level 3, and maybe the rest to level 1 each.. but we'll see. <br>
<br>
<br>
Right now, I'm having so much fun with Spellcasting Mastery and my new spells ... it's such a blast. Speaking of blasts, I still need Judgement.. oh well. One day, I suppose. <br>
<br>
I need a wealthy benefactor. <br>
<br>
WTB Wealthy Benefactor! PST!<br>
*giggles*<br>
