<br>
SCFury sounds interesting because of the crits on procs from the summoned hammer... I'd like to see those.  I'm just getting hit often enough, and getting annoyed by being interrupted enough that I feel like working on avoidance AAs (Combat Agility and Lightning Reflexes).<br>
<br>
I really love crit heals, too, and healing adept is fun with those, too, because your crits get bigger, too (like if you get adept 3, complete heals are 8250 instead of 7500, but crits are 16500 instead of 15000, for example).<br>
<br>
I see from your magelo you made 56, woohoo <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   And your equipment is looking very nice.  Have you thought about trying to get an Idol of the Underking from the Hole?  The camp is the ratman jail, and it's kind of a fun place.  The named rat is tough compared to the regular ones, and the ratman guard (instead of ratman warrior) for the SK epic is also kind of tough, but a good group around your level would do fine, I'm sure.  It's a rare drop from a rare spawn, but if you're planning on doing lots of AAs between levels, then it might be worth it, as it'll last through level 60, and then sell for a decent amount later on if you stop using level 60 or lower heals.<br>
<br>
If you run across any extra copies of Remove Greater Curse (54, but yeah right, who ever has an extra of that hehe), Stun Command (55), Aegis (57), The Unspoken Word (59), Banishment of Shadows (60) and/or Marzin's Mark (60, but again, yeah right, hehe), let me know, I'm buying! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
